body:
Hello, in the below code, I expect the call to `nth` on the mapped iterator to take advantage of my `nth` implementation. However, it does not, and instead calls `next` 5 times.  A Discord user suggested I open an issue here.

```rust
struct Custom { count: usize, max: usize }

impl Iterator for Custom {
    type Item = usize;
    
    fn next(&mut self) -> Option<usize> {
        println!("Call to next!");
        if self.count >= self.max { return None };
        let to_return = self.count;
        self.count += 1;
        return Some(to_return);
    }
    
    fn nth(&mut self, val: usize) -> Option<usize> {
        self.count += val;
        if self.count >= self.max { return None; }
        return Some(self.count);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let mut c = Custom { count: 0, max: 10000 };
    println!("5th value: {}", c.nth(5).unwrap());
    
    c = Custom { count: 0, max: 10000 };
    println!("5th mapped value: {}", c.map(|x| x * 2).nth(5).unwrap());
}
```

([Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=1ddfc825617f792cbcf4e317fb9b82c3))

Output:

```
